The paper deals with team optimal control of decentralized systems, which involves the coordination of multiple agents. This suggests that the paper could belong to the cs.SY (Systems and Control) sub-category. The paper also deals with optimization problems involving linear dynamics and quadratic costs, which are common in the cs.GT (Game Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of linear control strategies, which are relevant to the cs.LG (Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper provides generalizations to various scenarios, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category.
